               responsible for MLL functions in various developmental
               processes. The stability of MLL(N) is dependent on its
               intramolecular interaction with MLL(C), which is mediated
               through the first and fourth plant homeodomain (PHD) fingers
               (PHD1 and PHD4) and the phenylalanine/tyrosine-rich (FYRN)
