               sleep restores the critical state resulting in recovered
               power-law characteristics in activity and variability of
               synchronization. These findings support the intriguing
               hypothesis that sleep may be important to reorganize cortical
               network dynamics to a critical state thereby assuring optimal
               computational capabilities for the following time awake.",
